The paper proposes a new method for representation learning on graphs that improves the state-of-the-art performance for several graph tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed method involves the transformation of adjacency matrices, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) for tasks such as image and text classification. Finally, the paper also conducts experiments on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
